RESULTS: Changes in delta bandpower showed the highest and most consistent pattern of correlations with longitudinal changes in neuropsychological testing. The highest correlation was between delta bandpower increase and decline in the Rey Auditory-Verbal Learning Test (-0.59:p \ensuremath{<} 0.001). Delta bandpower was also increased in the incident dementia group compared to non-dementia at followup.
